“It’s time for Republicans to mature,” Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid says in a new tweet. For good measure, the graphic his office has put together even spells out “Grow Up” in building blocks. It’s a cute idea, but we have to take issue with Reid’s idea that “it’s time to move on” is the message to take from what Americans are saying loudly and clearly.

An NBC/Wall Street Journal poll released just this week, for example, shows that one-third of Americans who already have health insurance believe they’ll be worse off under Obamacare, while among the uninsured, 76 percent said they don’t understand the law and how it affects them.

But if polls aren’t Harry Reid’s thing, the American people did speak loudly and clearly on Obamacare on Sept. 12, 2009, and it looked like this.

